posts.title: ❗❗❗❗ Microsoft Spying Alert ❗❗❗
posts.content:
Hello Fellow Pedes , this is a Tech PSA:

If your PC recently installed Microsoft's newest update "24H2" - there is a new feature that gets installed called "Windows Recall"

This feature is an AI program that will essentially record your screen for all activity and has the ability to report it back to MS. To check if you have this feature installed, open up Powershell from the start menu (in admin mode) and run this command:

Dism /Online /Get-Featureinfo /Featurename:Recall

If the feature is installed, it will report its current state as being "Enabled" or "Disabled"

You can disable it by running the following command:

Dism /Online /Disable-Feature /Featurename:Recall

As of now, only CO-Pilot PC can use this feature, but it gets installed on all PCs with this update regardless, and if your PC does not meet the specs, disabling it by the above methods are the only way possible ATM that I know of.

More details can be found online on various Tech Blogs. You can also watch this video here that goes into some details on this feature.

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=M5p0a4-fnsM

Please only perform operations on your PC if you understand what you are doing.

Stay Safe Frens
